				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Rahsennor wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">1) update all platforms first, storing a delta of how far each one moves<br />2) any entity that collides with the top of a platform gets moved by the delta amount, without changing its velocity</div><br />That's pretty much my approach. The &quot;speed&quot; fields platform objects indicate how much they moved, so whenever an object's &quot;standing on&quot; field points to a moving platform, the displacement of the platform is added to the object's position, in addition to its own displacement.</div><br /><br />Hey, that sounds like how I did it.<br /><br />Also, in my game I allow enemies to walk on platforms.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

